## 1. Fix `ArmEnvironment.cs` line 80

Replace `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` in the `ToString()` method with a manual string that doesn't use reflection-based serialization:

Current:
```csharp
public override string ToString() => JsonSerializer.Serialize(this);
```

Replace with:
```csharp
public override string ToString() => $"{{\"Endpoint\":\"{Endpoint}\",\"Audience\":\"{Audience}\"}}";
```

## 2. Fix `ArmClientOptions.cs` line 52

Replace `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span)` with an AOT-safe approach using `JsonDocument`:

Current code (lines 51-52):
```csharp
var span = BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory().Span;
var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);
```

Replace with:
```csharp
var jsonDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(BinaryData.FromStream(stream));
var allProfile = jsonDoc.RootElement;
var armProfile = allProfile.GetProperty("resource-manager");
```

And then update the rest of the method to work with `JsonElement` instead of dictionaries. The full method body after the `using (Stream stream = ...)` line should become:

```csharp
{
    var jsonDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(BinaryData.FromStream(stream));
    var allProfile = jsonDoc.RootElement;
    var armProfile = allProfile.GetProperty("resource-manager");
    foreach (var namespaceProperty in armProfile.EnumerateObject())
    {
        var namespaceName = namespaceProperty.Name;
        var element = namespaceProperty.Value;

        foreach (var apiVersionProperty in element.EnumerateObject())
        {
            var apiVersion = apiVersionProperty.Name;
            foreach (var resourceTypeItem in apiVersionProperty.Value.EnumerateArray())
            {
                string resourceTypeName = default;
                foreach (var property in resourceTypeItem.EnumerateObject())
                {
                    if (property.NameEquals("resourceType"))
                    {
                        resourceTypeName = property.Value.GetString();
                        break;
                    }
                }
                var resourceType = $"{namespaceName}/{resourceTypeName}";
                ResourceApiVersionOverrides[resourceType] = apiVersion;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Also remove `using System.Collections.Generic;` and `using System.Text.Json;` from the usings at the top ONLY IF they are no longer used. Actually `System.Text.Json` is still needed for `JsonDocument` and `JsonElement`. But `System.Collections.Generic` is still used for `IDictionary`. Keep both.

## 3. Fix `Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs` line 30

The method calls `RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration)` which is marked `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]`. Add the appropriate attributes to the method:

Current:
```csharp
public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
    where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
{
    return builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration);
}
```

Replace with:
```csharp
[RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
[RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires dynamic code generation. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
    where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
{
    return builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration);
}
```

Make sure `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` is present in that file.

## 4. Fix `ArmOperation.cs` - the `IsResource<T>()` method (around lines 96-111)

Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` annotation to the generic type parameter:

